This paper deals with de novo DNA assembly, which is a fundamental task in Bioinformatics. It proposes a new approach to navigating de Bruijn graphs, which are commonly used in DNA assembly, and uses succinct data structures to represent the graphs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves computational biology and bioinformatics, which suggests cs.BIO (Bioinformatics) as the second likely category. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely categories. Finally, the paper involves computational geometry, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible category.
